Hungarian Stocks Advance Most in Week, Forint Gains Versus Euro

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-06-21T08:56:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/hungarian-stocks-advance-most-in-week-as-otp-bank-leads-gains.html
Hungarian shares rose the most in a
week and the forint gained as concern eased that  Greece  will
default and spread the crisis to other indebted European
nations.  The benchmark BUX index of shares jumped as much as 0.8
percent to 22,656.42, the biggest intraday gain since June 14,
and traded 0.4 percent higher at 10:24 a.m. in Budapest. The
Hungarian currency appreciated 0.6 percent to 266.79 per euro.  Luxembourg Prime Minister  Jean-Claude Juncker , head of the
euro-region finance ministers’ group, said yesterday Greek Prime
Minister  George Papandreou  assured him the government would do
everything to ensure financial aid before a confidence vote
today.  “The Luxembourg prime minister calmed those who were
getting nervous, so the forint started off in the direction of
267” per euro, traders at Commerzbank AG led by Peter Karsai in
Budapest wrote in a note to clients today.  OTP Bank Nyrt., the country’s biggest lender, advanced 1
percent to 5,758 forint, and Gedeon Richter Nyrt., the largest
drugmaker, added 0.6 percent to 36,345 forint.  Hungary’s debt level will fall 4 percentage points after
the Cabinet, which funneled private pension funds to the state,
will today announce a decision to use the proceeds to cut debt,
Magyar Radio said, citing Prime Minister  Viktor Orban . The debt
level will fall 1.35 trillion forint ($7.2 billion) to 77
percent of gross domestic product, from 81 percent, the public
radio said on its website, citing an interview with Orban.  To contact the reporter on this story:
